The EIOPA governance requirements for fit and proper persons are as follows:

*   **Fit Requirements**: National competent authorities should ensure that persons who effectively run the undertaking or hold key functions (including members of the management, supervisory, or administrative body) are "fit" [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements]. This includes ensuring a diversity of relevant experience, knowledge, and qualifications to ensure professional management and oversight [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements]. Collectively, members of the administrative, management, or supervisory body must possess appropriate knowledge, experience, and qualification in:
    *   Financial markets and insurance [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   Business model and business strategy [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   System of governance [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   Actuarial and financial analysis [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements];
    *   Requirements and regulatory framework [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements].
*   **Proper Requirements**: When assessing if a person is "proper," the undertaking must assess their financial soundness and honesty [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements]. This assessment is based on evidence of business conduct, personal behaviour, and character, including supervisory, financial, or criminal aspects regardless of jurisdiction [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0012__guideline-11-fit-requirements].
*   **Policies and Procedures**: Undertakings must have a fit and proper policy that includes:
    *   Procedures for assessing the propriety and fitness of key functions and those effectively running the undertaking, both on an on-going basis and when being considered for a position [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0014__guideline-13-fit-and-proper-policies-and];
    *   A description of situations that necessitate a re-assessment of these requirements [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0014__guideline-13-fit-and-proper-policies-and];
    *   Internal standards and procedures for assessing other relevant personnel not subject to Article 42 of the Solvency II Directive, both on an on-going basis and during initial consideration for a position [eiopa_guidelines_system_of_governance__0014__guideline-13-fit-and-proper-policies-and].
